      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:136:23",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/136/23",
      "text": [
        " «نَعَمْ إِنَّمَا لَهُ مَا نَوَى."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3065 - Ali ibn Ja'far asked his brother Imam Musa ibn Jafar Al-Kadhim (as) about a sacrificial animal: if the one slaughtering it mistakenly mentions a name other than its owner, does it suffice for the owner of the sacrifice?\nImam (as) replied: \"Yes, it is for the one who intended it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
